node.title: Victoria records 1,185 new COVID-19 cases and seven deaths
node.alt: A nurse dressed in a pale yellow PPE gown is pictured from behind pushing a bed through the corridor of the Alfred Hospital.
node.description: There are now 13,050 active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 566 people have died during the state's current Delta outbreak.
node.content:
["Victoria has recorded 1,185\u00a0new local COVID-19 cases and seven\u00a0deaths.", "There are now 13,050\u00a0active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 566\u00a0people have died during the state's current Delta outbreak.", "There are 297\u00a0people in hospital with COVID-19, of whom 47\u00a0are in intensive care and 25\u00a0are on a ventilator.", "The health department said a further 55\u00a0people were in intensive care but their COVID-19 infections were no longer considered active.", "The new cases were detected from 52,257\u00a0test results received yesterday.", "There were 3,769\u00a0doses of vaccine administered at state-run sites yesterday, and more vaccinations at GP clinics and other venues.", "Victoria has now fully vaccinated more than 91\u00a0per cent of its population aged 12 and over.", "More to come.", "", "
Why we hear about some COVID-19 variants more than others
"]
